definitions.definition: comparative form of little : more little ; of inferior size, degree or extent; smaller , lesser .
labels: Now chiefly of numbers or dimensions
definitions.label_groups: Now chiefly of numbers or dimensions

definitions.definition: A smaller amount of; not as much.
examples: No less than eight pints of beer.
I have less tea than coffee.
You have even less sense than an inanimate object.
There are less people here now.
Now there are three less green bottles hanging on the wall.

main_definition: ( Now chiefly of numbers or dimensions ) comparative form of little : more little ; of inferior size, degree or extent; smaller , lesser . [from 11th c.]
secondary_definitions: A smaller amount of; not as much. [from 12th c.]
( proscribed ) Fewer ; a smaller number of. [from 9th c. at latest]
